<s> John Gunderson gave a great presentation at CSUN (http://www.csun.edu/cod/conf2001/proceedings/0095gunderson.html) on a tool he has developed for converting PowerPoint to html.  </s>
<s> This would be another way to have accessible PowerPoint.  </s>
<s> The tool is available at http://www.rehab.uiuc.edu/ppt/.  </s>
<s> Here's what he says there.  </s>
<s> This Power Point Accessibility Wizard offers an alternative to PowerPoint's Web publishing feature.  </s>
<s> The standard Power Point Web Publishing option creates XML based web content that can only be used by Microsoft Internet Explorer.  </s>
<s> Even if non-XML options are selected, users cannot easily add information that is required for accessibility.  </s>
<s> This Power Point Accessibility Wizard simplifies the task of converting PowerPoint presentations to text pure HTML through an easy- to-use user interface, and automates much of the conversion of Power Point Presentations to an HTML format that includes required accessibility information.  </s>
